The paper discusses the use of gradient-based methods in machine learning, specifically in the context of games such as generative adversarial networks (GANs) and actor-critic systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), game theory (cs.GT), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely category as it is the primary focus of the paper, while the other categories are relevant due to the specific applications discussed in the paper.
